# Unfocused Mode

Unfocused Mode is the inline editing state: the WYSIWYG editor is active but not fullscreen. The editor is rendered on the readonly page with the live-edit controls bar overlay. All logic lives in `live-wysiwyg-integration.js`.

## Controls Bar

The controls bar (`.live-edit-controls`) is provided by the upstream `mkdocs-live-edit-plugin`. It contains Edit, Save, Cancel, Rename, Delete, New buttons and the "Live Edit:" label. The WYSIWYG plugin does not modify the controls bar structure or padding.

## Width Alignment

Editing surfaces use negative horizontal margins (`-10px`) to extend through the controls bar padding and align with the readonly content width. The `<style id="live-wysiwyg-width-overrides">` block is injected in `replaceTextareaWithWysiwyg` and removed in the destroy path. Do not remove controls padding; use the negative-margin approach on editing surfaces only. See `layout.mdc` for the authoritative width alignment rules.

## Toggle Button Injection

`ensureToggleButton` injects the WYSIWYG/textarea toggle button into the controls bar. It is called from `observeForTextarea` and when the editor activates. The button is inserted before the label's next sibling (or as first child). `removeToggleButton` removes it on destroy.

## Scroll Suppression During Focus Mode

When focus mode is active (Layer 2 in the mode hierarchy), unfocused mode's document-level scrolling is disabled via `overflow: hidden` on both `document.body` and `document.documentElement`. Permanent document-level event handlers from `captureReadModeSelectionOnChange` (`selectionchange`, `mousedown`, `scroll`) include `if (isFocusModeActive) return;` guards to prevent execution during focus mode. See `modes-of-operation.mdc` for the suppression contract.

## Transition to Focus Mode

The user enters Focus Mode via the Focus Mode toolbar button (expand icon) or browser fullscreen. `enterFocusMode` reparents the toolbar and editor wrapper into the focus overlay. Cursor and selection are captured before reparenting and restored after.
